              "fontSize": 12,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "ionyR",
              "name": "Dashboard-populated-final",
              "context": "<!--\n## Dashboard-populated-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** populated\n**Component:** Dashboard\n\n### Purpose\nDefault landing for a signed-in user with one or more connected repos. All repos from every workspace the user belongs to land in a single scrollable list (build plan lines 123–134).\n\n### Design notes\n- Page bg #f6f6f9; list panel surface #ffffff with 1px #dfe0e7 and radius 16.\n- Page header sits above the list: title 'All repos' Geist 22/500 #121111, mono count badge, right-side filter chips ('All', 'Personal', 'Team Acme'), sort 'Last sync' button.\n- Repo rows are 56px tall, single line. Mono org/repo (Geist Mono 14 #121111), workspace chip on the right, status dot, relative timestamp.\n- One row is rendered in its hover state to show revealed actions (Open / Re-sync / Pin) on the right edge.\n- One row demonstrates 'syncing' (status dot + 'Syncing…' meta), one 'failed' (red dot + Retry on hover), one 'stale' (muted ring + 'Stale').\n- No card grids, no tiles. Density wins.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Sibling layouts: Dashboard-empty-final, Dashboard-expanded-final.\n- Each row variant lives in the component kit as RepoRow-{state}-final.\n- WorkspaceChip variants: WorkspaceChip-personal-final, WorkspaceChip-team-final.\n-->",
              "clip": true,
              "width": 1440,
              "height": 1080,
              "fill": "#f6f6f9ff",
              "cornerRadius": 16,
